Good morning team, I hope you are doing well.
Is there any way to set up and edit conditional options via API for a property?
I saw this inspecting the HubSpot UI when I set up a conditional logic property:

POST <https://app-eu1.HubSpot.com/api/conditional-properties/v2/options/batch/replace>?

[
    {
        "dependentFieldName": "modelo",
        "controllingFieldName": "marca",
        "optionRules": [
            {
                "controllingFieldValue": "Abarth",
                "dependentOptions": [
                    "100 Nx",
                    "F900R"
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
]

but I think it's not public. Any way I can use it?

Hi all, can anyone confirm if this is a bug on the HubSpots API please?

Im using the <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/cms/pages|pages CMS api> and when I fetch a specific page from this endpoint: *`/cms/v3/pages/site-pages/{objectId}`* its supposed to return the following:
```{
 ...
 ...
 ...
 widgets: {
   // list of widgets
 },
 ...
 ...
}```
But the widgets list is always being returned an empty array  `widgets: {}`

In my page template I have the following:
```   {% module_block module "mt_sticky_anchors" path="../modules/mt-sticky-anchors" no_wrapper=true%}
      {% module_attribute "menu_items" is_json=true %} 
        [
          { "item_label": "Digital solutions", "section_id": "section-digital-solutions" },
          { "item_label": "01 Connect", "section_id": "section-connect" },
          { "item_label": "02 Automate", "section_id": "section-automate" }
      ]
      {% end_module_attribute %}
    {% end_module_block %}```
If I replace the `module_block` with `widget_block` then the API response includes the widgets. Would love to get some feedback from HubSpots team on this
